source.name: DTIC Corporate Source
source.description: The Defense Technical Information Center (DTIC) maintains a Corporate Source Authority System (CSAS) which lists all organizations that have contributed information to any of DTIC's three major databases. The DTIC Corporate Source database is a collection of Corporate Authors.  Corporate Authors are the organizations and agencies responsible for reports received by DTIC.  Each record displays the standardized form of the organization's name, the organization's parent and suborganizations, and the organization's Source Code.  A Source Code is a unique numeric designation assigned by DTIC to each organization in the database.
